 strong="H3478">Israel</char>. <verse eid="EZR 3:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="EZR 3:11" />And they sang together by <char style="w" strong="H6030">course</char> in <char style="w" strong="H1984">praising</char> and giving <char style="w" strong="H3034">thanks</char> unto the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>; because <char style="add">he is</char> <char style="w" strong="H2896">good</char>, for his <char style="w" strong="H2617">mercy</char> <char style="add">endureth</char> for <char style="w" strong="H5769">ever</char> toward <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>. And all the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> <char style="w" strong="H7321">shouted</char> with a <char style="w" strong="H1419">great</char> <char style="w" strong="H8643">shout</char>, when they <char style="w" strong="H1984">praised</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, because the <char style="w" strong="H3245">foundation</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> was <char style="w" strong="H3245">laid</char>. <verse eid="EZR 3:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="EZR 3:12" />But <char style="w" strong="H7227">many</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H3548">priests</char> and <char style="w" strong="H3881">Levites</char> and <char style="w" strong="H7218">chief</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H0001">fathers</char>, <char style="add">who were</char> ancient <char style="w" strong="H2205">men</char>, that had <char style="w" strong="H7200">seen</char> the <char style="w" strong="H7223">first</char> <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>, when the <char style="w" strong="H3245">foundation</char> of this <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> was <char style="w" strong="H3245">laid</char> before their <char style="w" strong="H5869">eyes</char>, <char style="w" strong="H1058">wept</char> with a